## Context
The §2.x passage where the 2007/Stern moment is said to "create the conditions for
a new kind of economic object" was flagged as too strong (R2y), and the
surrounding performativity argument is declarative rather than explanatory.
Tracker: 0141. R2.21 (ticket 0136) already narrowed the datable claim — this child
handles the performativity and politically-binding passages, not a re-narrowing.

## Relevant passages
- `content/manuscript.qmd` §2.x/p12 — political legitimacy introduced "suddenly"
  (R2x); UNFCCC-2007 + Stern "created the conditions" (R2y); "required not just
  models but accounting infrastructure" (R2z); performativity argument (p12); how
  climate finance became politically binding (R2ad).

## Actions
1. p12 political legitimacy: say why it becomes a concern at this stage and for
   whom (R2x).
2. Demonstrate carefully or soften the 2007/Stern "created the conditions" claim
   (R2y), consistent with the R2.21 narrowing already made.
3. Make "required not just models but accounting infrastructure" concrete (R2z;
   cf. R1j at p3 — coordinate with 0139 on the models-vs-infrastructure framing).
4. Turn the performativity argument from declarative to explanatory: name the
   apparatus, methodologies, consequences (p12).
5. Name the institutional/legal mechanisms by which climate finance became
   politically binding (R2ad).

## Test (prose ratchet)
- Negative guard only; no strengthening of the 2007/Stern break (methodological
  honesty: computation corroborates, does not endogenise — see writing.md).

## Exit criteria
- [ ] §2.x performativity + politically-binding passages revised, explanatory not declarative
- [ ] 2007/Stern claim consistent with the R2.21 narrowing
- [ ] Cover-letter traceability rows (R2x, R2y, R2z, R2ad) updated with §ref + commit SHA
- [ ] Prose in the author's voice per `docs/style-anchor-v205.md`; `make check-fast` green
